  _designationBase: PF-440
  _frameName: Tanto
  _frameClass: Interceptor
  _callsignGroup: 0
  _factionKey: Stock/Alliance
  _silhouette: {fileID: 0}
  _hudSilhouette: {fileID: 0}
  _hudSilhouetteGroup: {fileID: 0}
  _enemyIconType: 1
  _screenshot: {fileID: 0}
  _longDescription: $CRAFT_TANTO_DESC
  _flavorText: 'My beloved Tanto. Believe it or not, my job in the Alliance isn''t
    to be a tactical advisor, it''s piloting these.


    Pride of Mackinaw Aerospace,
    designed during the Deshima Blitz when Deshiman Praetor Robin Vicoss decided
    that the sons of bitches on Badnarik were going down. The siege lasted long enough
    that the Graznovian techs managed to roll out a few prototypes towards the end
    of the Blitz, but the Trident was still the poster-boy fighter at that point
    and the Tanto only had brief combat engagements fighting the Skirvaldr.


    This
    is all of that delicious Graznovian engineering that the Naval Office salivates
    over, just now the latter could actually get their clammy hands on it. First
    order of business with the Naval Office was fighting over whether it should be
    atmo (replacing the Lancer) or vacuum only (replacing the Trident), eventually
    settling on a compromise and giving us the worst of both options- multidomain.
    Twin SD-1000s built by Freke give it the reliability for both domains while not
    being very good at either, but that''s what happens when you roll the dice with
    the ANO.


    On the upside, the Tanto is one of the most flexible spacecraft
    you''ll find in the Archipelago- if it fits on any of the other craft, chances
    are it''ll find a home on the Tanto.


    - T.Meadows, LT'
